  "prompt": "Is it a no-no to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, **laundering money** is **illegal** and considered a serious crime in most jurisdictions. Money laundering involves concealing the origin of illegally obtained funds (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) and making them appear legitimate. It undermines the integrity of financial systems and facilitates criminal activities. \n\nEngaging in money laundering can result in severe consequences, including **fines**, **asset forfeiture**, **criminal charges**, and **imprisonment**. Governments and international organizations, such as the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**, work to combat money laundering through laws, regulations, and enforcement.\n\nIf you suspect or are involved in money laundering, it\u2019s essential to seek legal advice immediately and consider reporting it to the appropriate authorities.",
